# AGENTS.md — {{Project Name}}

**Task-ownership coordination for concurrent AI sessions.** Read this at the start of every session **before editing any file**.

> This file is the **coordination layer** for parallel work. It is *not* methodology canon (that's CLAUDE.md) and *not* a runtime artifact — it is an ephemeral, human-edited board of "who owns what right now." When a task is done and merged, remove its claim.

> **When you need this:** only when `worktree_isolation: auto` (multiple sessions or multiple developers on this repo — see `CLAUDE.local.md ## Branching`). For a single developer running one session at a time, this file stays empty and can be ignored.

---

## Why (the collision class)

When N developers × M sessions touch one repo, two things break:

1. **Silent branch swap** — two sessions in the *same working directory*: one runs `git checkout`, the other's files change underneath it without warning. Fix attempts then corrupt state.
2. **Same-file overwrite** — two sessions edit the same file on different branches → merge conflict on PR (industry measure: ~27.67% of AI-agent PRs conflict).

This methodology solves it with **four layers** (see [ADR-002](docs/adr/ADR-002-branching-mode-contract.md) § Concurrent-Session Isolation):

| Layer | What | Prevents |
|---|---|---|
| 1. **Isolation** | git worktree per session (Claude Code `-w` / `isolation: worktree`) | *silent* overwrite |
| 2. **Ownership** | this file — one file, one owner | the same-file conflict *before it happens* |
| 3. **Staging** | worktree + branch + PR (nothing reaches main without merge) | uncorrected mutations landing |
| 4. **Merge-gate** | `team`-mode PR review | whatever 1-3 missed — surfaces as a *visible* conflict |

**Worktrees make conflicts honest** (visible on PR) instead of silent (lost work). **This file (encapsulation) is what actually prevents the conflict** by not handing overlapping file-scopes to concurrent sessions.

